.TH NFUZZ 1 "March 2026" "nmap-xyberpix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nfuzz \- raw IPv4 / stream / Bluetooth L2CAP mutation harness and optional HTTP browser\-fuzz server (nmap-xyberpix)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SS Raw IPv4 mode
.B nfuzz
.RB [ \-\-authorized ]
.RB [ \-\-dst
.IR ADDR ]
.RB [ \-\-hex
.IR HEX | \-\-hex\-file
.IR PATH | \-\-pcap
.IR PATH | \-\-template
.IR NAME ]
.RI [ options ]
.SS Stream mode (TCP or UDP payload)
.B nfuzz
.B \-\-authorized
.BI \-\-proto " tcp|udp"
.BI \-\-dst " ADDR"
.BI \-\-dport " PORT"
.RB [ \-\-hex
.IR HEX | \-\-hex\-file
.IR PATH ]
.RI [ options ]
.SS Bluetooth L2CAP mode (macOS or Linux)
.B nfuzz
.B \-\-authorized
.BI \-\-bt\-l2cap " BD_ADDR"
.RB [ \-\-hex
.IR HEX | \-\-hex\-file
.IR PATH ]
.RI [ options ]
.SS HTTP browser fuzz daemon
.B nfuzz
.B \-\-authorized
.B \-\-http-daemon
.RI [ http-options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nfuzz
supports several modes. In
.B raw
mode it sends mutated IPv4 datagrams using a raw socket
.RB ( IP_HDRINCL ).
In
.B stream
mode it connects or sends UDP datagrams to an IPv4 host and mutates an
application\-layer payload (no raw socket).
On builds with Bluetooth L2CAP support
.RB ( \-\-bt\-l2cap ;
macOS uses
.BR IOBluetooth ,
Linux uses BlueZ),
it can mutate payloads over an L2CAP connection.
In
.B HTTP
mode it listens on a TCP port and serves a
.B new
HTML document (with embedded fuzzed JavaScript and stressed markup) on every
request, so a browser pointed at the URL continuously exercises the DOM, HTML,
and JS parsers (use only in an authorized lab).
.PP
The HTTP daemon locates the header/body delimiter without treating the request
as a NUL\-terminated C string, so embedded NUL bytes cannot hide the end of
headers.
.B \-\-browser\-url
(and the URL derived from
.BR \-\-http\-bind )
must not contain ASCII control bytes or DEL.
.B \-\-hex\-file
must name a regular file; on systems with
.BR O_NOFOLLOW ,
symlinks are not followed.
.B \-\-pid\-file
is written without following symbolic links where the OS supports that flag.
.PP
You must pass
.B \-\-authorized
or set
.B NFUZZ_AUTHORIZED=1
in the environment before the tool will run.
.PP
Raw mode: the base packet is hexadecimal (see
.BR \-\-hex " or " \-\-hex\-file ),
the
.IR N th
IPv4 datagram from a
.BR \-\-pcap
file (via libpcap, similar to Scapy
.BR rdpcap ),
or a built\-in IPv4 stack chosen with
.BR \-\-template
.RB ( icmp\-echo ", " udp ", " tcp\-syn ;
layered similarly to interactive packet tools such as Scapy).
The IPv4 version nibble must be 4 for hex input. Typical use requires superuser privileges.
HTTP mode does not require raw socket privileges.
Stream mode does not require raw socket privileges (TCP/UDP only).
L2CAP mode uses the system Bluetooth stack (macOS may prompt for Bluetooth access; Linux may require capabilities; see local policy).
.PP
In the foreground (without
.BR \-\-detach ),
each accepted TCP connection is logged to standard error as one line: client
IPv4 address and port, HTTP method and request target parsed from the first
non\-empty line, the status code returned (or
.B dropped
if the response could not be built), and the fuzzed HTML body size in bytes.
Detached servers skip this logging because standard error is typically closed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-authorized
Required acknowledgement of legal authorization (or
.BR NFUZZ_AUTHORIZED=1 ).
.SS HTTP daemon
.TP
.B \-\-http\-daemon
Run the HTTP fuzz server instead of raw IPv4 sends.
.TP
.BI \-\-http\-bind " HOST:PORT"
Listen address (default
.BR 127.0.0.1:8787 ).
Non\-loopback binds require
.BR \-\-http\-allow\-remote .
.TP
.BI \-\-http\-max\-body " N"
Maximum HTML body size in bytes (default 262144, max 524288).
.TP
.BI \-\-http\-refresh " SEC"
HTML meta refresh interval to reload
.B /
(0 disables; default 2).
.TP
.B \-\-http\-allow\-remote
Allow binding outside 127.0.0.0/8 (authorized environments only).
.TP
.B \-\-detach
Double\-fork to the background and detach from the terminal (HTTP mode only).
.TP
.BI \-\-pid\-file " PATH"
Write the process ID after the server is listening (HTTP mode; useful with
.BR \-\-detach ).
Refuses to open through a symbolic link where
.B O_NOFOLLOW
is available.
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-browser
Spawn a headless browser process that loads the fuzz URL (URL is passed as the
last argument to the browser). The server uses a short
.BR poll (2)
timeout so it can supervise and optionally restart the child. Requires
.BR \-\-http\-daemon .
.TP
.BI \-\-browser\-cmd " CMD"
Executable name or path for
.BR \-\-auto\-browser
(default:
.B NFUZZ_BROWSER_CMD
from the environment, or
.BR chromium ).
Must be a single
.BR execvp (3)
token: no ASCII control bytes (including DEL) or shell metacharacters
.RB ( ; | ` $ & ).
.TP
.BI \-\-browser\-preset " NAME"
Headless-oriented defaults prepended before
.B \-\-browser\-arg
entries:
.B chromium
(new headless flags, no sandbox),
.B firefox
.RB ( \-\-headless ),
or
.B none
(user supplies flags via
.BR \-\-browser\-arg ).
Default:
.BR chromium .
.TP
.BI \-\-browser\-restart\-sec " N"
If
.I N
is greater than zero, send
.B SIGTERM
to the browser and start a fresh process every
.I N
seconds. If zero, the browser is restarted only when it exits.
.TP
.BI \-\-browser\-url " URL"
Open this URL instead of deriving
.B http://HOST:PORT/
from
.BR \-\-http\-bind .
When the bind address is
.BR 0.0.0.0 ,
the derived URL uses
.B 127.0.0.1
as the host unless overridden here.
The URL must not contain ASCII control bytes or DEL (it is passed as one
.BR execvp (3)
argument).
.TP
.BI \-\-browser\-arg " ARG"
Extra argument inserted before the URL (repeatable; maximum 32).
Each argument must satisfy the same token rules as
.BR \-\-browser\-cmd .
.SS Stream mode (TCP/UDP)
Mutually exclusive with raw IPv4 options
.RB ( \-\-template ", " \-\-pcap ", fragmentation, " \-\-patch\-addresses ", " \-\-src ", IP/TCP option knobs)
and with
.BR \-\-bt\-l2cap .
Requires
.B \-\-dst
and a non\-zero
.BR \-\-dport .
.TP
.BI \-\-proto " tcp|udp"
Use a stream socket
.RB ( TCP )
or datagram socket
.RB ( UDP )
to
.BR \-\-dst :\-\-dport
instead of raw IPv4.
.TP
.BI \-\-proto\-payload\-len " N"
When
.B \-\-hex
and
.B \-\-hex\-file
are omitted, allocate
.I N
zero bytes as the base payload (default 256).
.TP
.B \-\-proto\-reconnect
TCP only: perform a fresh connect for each iteration (default is one connection for the whole run).
.TP
.BI \-\-proto\-connect\-timeout " SEC"
TCP connect wait in seconds (default 10, range 1\(en300).
.SS Bluetooth L2CAP mode
Available when
.B nfuzz
was built with Bluetooth support (macOS
.BR IOBluetooth ;
Linux
.BR \-lbluetooth ).
Mutually exclusive with raw mode and
.BR \-\-proto .
.TP
.BI \-\-bt\-l2cap " ADDR"
Peer Bluetooth address
.RB ( XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX ).
.TP
.BI \-\-bt\-psm " N"
L2CAP PSM in host byte order (default 4097).
.SS Raw IPv4 mode
.TP
.BI \-\-dst " ADDR"
Destination IPv4 address (used for
.BR sendto (2)
and, with
.BR \-\-patch\-addresses ,
written into the IPv4 header).
.TP
.BI \-\-src " ADDR"
When combined with
.BR \-\-patch\-addresses ,
overwrites the IPv4 source field (bytes 12\(en15).
.TP
.B \-\-patch-addresses
Patch IPv4 header source/destination from
.B \-\-src
and
.BR \-\-dst .
.TP
.BI \-\-hex " STRING"
Base datagram as an even\-length hex string (whitespace may appear only outside
the argument; use
.B \-\-hex\-file
for free\-form hex files).
.TP
.BI \-\-hex\-file " PATH"
Read base datagram from a file; non\-hex characters are treated as whitespace
and ignored.
The path must refer to a regular file; on systems with
.BR O_NOFOLLOW ,
symlinks are not followed.
.TP
.BI \-\-pcap " PATH"
Use the
.IR N th
IPv4 packet in a capture file as the base datagram (see
.BR \-\-pcap\-index ).
Link\-layer types supported include Ethernet (incl. 802.1Q),
.BR DLT_RAW ,
.BR DLT_NULL / DLT_LOOP ,
and Linux
.BR DLT_LINUX_SLL .
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-hex ", " \-\-hex\-file ", and " \-\-template .
.TP
.BI \-\-pcap\-index " N"
Select which IPv4 packet to use (1 = first IPv4 packet in file; default 1).
.TP
.BI \-\-template " NAME"
Build a minimal IPv4 datagram without hex:
.BR icmp\-echo ", " udp ", or " tcp\-syn .
Mutations default to the L4 payload region (after the fixed ICMP/UDP/TCP header).
.TP
.BI \-\-ip\-options\-hex " HEX"
Append raw IPv4 option bytes after the 20\-byte header (requires
.BR \-\-template ).
The implementation pads with IP NOP (1) to a 4\-byte boundary; at most 40 option bytes after padding.
.TP
.BI \-\-tcp\-options\-hex " HEX"
Append raw TCP option bytes after the 20\-byte TCP header (requires
.BR \-\-template " tcp\-syn" ).
Padded with TCP NOP (1) to a 4\-byte boundary; at most 40 option bytes after padding.
.TP
.BI \-\-tcp\-mss " N"
Prepend a standard MSS option (kind 2, length 4) before any
.BR \-\-tcp\-options\-hex
bytes
.RB ( tcp\-syn
only).
.TP
.BI \-\-sport " N"
.TP
.BI \-\-dport " N"
Source and destination ports for
.B udp
and
.B tcp\-syn
templates (0 selects built\-in defaults).
.TP
.BI \-\-payload\-len " N"
L4 payload size in bytes after the template header (0 uses defaults: 32 for ICMP echo, 16 for UDP, 0 for TCP SYN).
.TP
.BI \-\-icmp\-id " N"
.TP
.BI \-\-icmp\-seq " N"
ICMP echo identifier and sequence
.RB ( icmp\-echo
template only).
.TP
.BI \-\-tcp\-win " N"
TCP window for
.B tcp\-syn
(0 means 8192).
.TP
.BI \-\-frag\-mtu " BYTES"
If the datagram is larger than
.IR BYTES ,
emit RFC 791 IPv4 fragments that each fit within
.IR BYTES .
0 disables fragmentation (default). With
.BR \-r ","
rate limiting applies once per logical packet after all fragments are sent.
.TP
.BI \-c ", " \-\-count " N"
Number of packets to send (default 1, maximum 10,000,000).
.TP
.BI \-r ", " \-\-rate " RATE"
Sleep between packets to approximate
.I RATE
packets per second (0 = no limit).
.TP
.BI \-s ", " \-\-seed " N"
PRNG seed (default derived from time).
.TP
.BI \-S ", " \-\-strategy " NAME"
Mutation:
.BR bitflip ", " random_byte ", " inc_byte ", " dec_byte ", " truncate ", " append_random ", " shuffle_block .
.TP
.BI \-m ", " \-\-mutable\-off " O"
Start offset of the mutable region (default: end of IPv4 header).
.TP
.BI \-l ", " \-\-mutable\-len " L"
Length of mutable region (default: through packet end).
.PP
Stream and L2CAP modes use the same
.BR \-c ", " \-r ", " \-s ", " \-S ", " \-m ", and " \-l
controls on the application payload; default mutable region is the full base payload (offset 0).
.TP
.B \-\-fix\-ip\-len
Set IPv4 total length from buffer length (default: on).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-fix\-ip\-len
.TP
.B \-\-fix\-checksums
Recompute IPv4 header checksum (default: on).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-fix\-checksums
.TP
.B \-\-fix\-l4
Recompute UDP, TCP, or ICMPv4 checksum when the IPv4 protocol field matches.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NFUZZ_AUTHORIZED
If set to
.BR 1 ,
equivalent to
.BR \-\-authorized .
.TP
.B NFUZZ_BROWSER_CMD
Default browser executable for
.B \-\-auto\-browser
when
.B \-\-browser\-cmd
is not given.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non\-zero on usage errors, privilege/socket failures, or send errors.
.SH NOTES
Layered IPv4 templates and optional fragmentation follow the same composition ideas as
the Scapy project
.RB ( https://github.com/secdev/scapy ),
implemented here as a small single\-file C tool without a Python runtime.
.PP
.B nfuzz
does not perform IPv6 or link\-layer framing in the raw path. The HTTP server is
IPv4 only and is intentionally minimal (no TLS). It is not a replacement for
dedicated browser fuzzing frameworks; it complements higher\-level tools such as
the
.B proto\-generic\-fuzzer
NSE script.
.PP
Browser fuzzing can crash tabs or the whole browser; run only on disposable
profiles and isolated VMs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nmap (1),
.BR nping (1),
.BR pcap (3pcap)
.SH AUTHOR
nmap\-xyberpix
